      {
        "id": 3034129,
        "name": "Howard Cooper",
        "username": "Howard_Cooper",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/howard_cooper/{size}/700_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-11-25T12:55:15.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"165933\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Any comparison or contrast to Ramonet and Niellon?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I have only had Moreau\u2019s red Chassagne at a relatively young age (that will change now that I am building up a supply) but I like them very much.</p>\n<p>I have more experience with Ramonet\u2019s red Chassagne and I find them among the most seductive red Burgundies that I have had over the last several years.  If you value power over seductiveness, you may not like them as much as I do.</p>",
        "post_number": 6,
